{"build_type":"library","description":"The single declarative home of every numeric enforcement threshold (E2 family). Other packages never hardcode limits; they call these constant functions (module globals cannot carry the value: lowering emits all globals as zeroed data, init values are ignored). Current constants: limit_package_file_bytes() = 32768 (operator-locked 2026-06-10: hard physical limit on the RAW byte size of one .ipm package file, measured by the compiler driver on the text it just read, before parsing - lines are gameable by minification, bytes are not). Future E2 thresholds (per-function instruction count, function count per package, AST depth, locals count) are added here as further constant functions, one declarative place to review.","module_name":"declare-enforcement-threshold-numeric-values","package_name":"declare-enforcement-threshold-numeric-values","function_definitions":{"declare-enforcement-threshold-numeric-values":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"limit_value","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":32768},{"instruction_type":"return_statement","return_payload":{"value":"limit_value"}}]}}}